        // ── Dashboard Display Modes (Article) ────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Dashboard Display Modes — Focus & Ambient",
            Slug = "dashboard-display-modes",
            Summary = "Focus Mode strips the dashboard down to just your tasks and orders; Ambient Mode turns it into a full-screen status display. How to enter, exit, and what persists.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 4,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 6,
            AppRoutes = """["/dashboard"]""",
            Tags = """["dashboard","focus-mode","ambient-mode","display"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Dashboard Display Modes\n\nBesides the normal grid of cards, the Dashboard has two other views — **Focus Mode** and **Ambient Mode**. You switch to each from buttons in the dashboard header, and each is good for a different situation.\n\n### Focus Mode\n\nFocus Mode trims the dashboard down to the three things you personally act on: **My Tasks**, **Open Orders**, and the **End of Day** note. Everything else — the quick numbers, charts, team load — is hidden so you can concentrate without distraction.\n\n**Turning it on and off:** Click the **Focus Mode** button in the header. The button highlights while Focus Mode is on. Click it again, or use the X in the corner of the focus view, to go back to the full dashboard.\n\n**You can bookmark it.** When Focus Mode is on, you can bookmark or share the page and it will open straight into Focus Mode, and refreshing keeps you there. The dashboard also remembers your last choice.\n\n**One at a time.** Focus Mode and Ambient Mode can't both be on — turning on Focus Mode turns off Ambient Mode.\n\n### Ambient Mode\n\nAmbient Mode turns the dashboard into a full-screen status display you can read from across the room: a big clock and date, headline numbers (active jobs, overdue, hours today), and a short list of upcoming deadlines. It's made for a wall-mounted monitor or a screen you walk past — no controls to fuss with.\n\n**Turning it on:** Click the **Ambient** button in the header.\n\n**Turning on by itself:** The dashboard can also switch to Ambient Mode on its own after you've been idle for a while. You choose how long that wait is, and this never kicks in while you're editing your layout or already in Focus Mode, so it won't interrupt your work.\n\n**Getting out:** Ambient Mode is made to leave in an instant — press **Escape**, or just click anywhere, and you're back to the normal dashboard. A hint at the bottom of the screen reminds you.\n\n**Always current.** While in Ambient Mode, the display stays up to date: the clock ticks every second and the numbers and deadlines refresh on their own, so a wall display never goes stale.\n\n### Which to use when\n\n- **Heads-down on your own work?** Focus Mode — fewer cards, just your tasks, orders, and end-of-day note.\n- **Running a shared or wall monitor, or stepping away?** Ambient Mode — big clock, headline numbers, deadlines; leave with a tap or Escape.\n- **Everyday work?** The normal grid of cards, which you can tailor with the Customize button.","sections":[]}"""
