            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Reference,
            EstimatedMinutes = 4,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 90,
            AppRoutes = """["/dashboard"]""",
            Tags = """["dashboard","reference","advanced"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## The Grid Adjusts to Your Screen\n\nThe dashboard grid reshapes itself to fit the space it has, rather than sticking to one fixed layout. On a narrow screen (under about 768 pixels wide) cards stack into a single column; on a medium screen they spread across six columns; on a wide screen they use the full twelve. It watches the available width and re-flows the cards live — so resizing your window or collapsing the sidebar rearranges them instantly, with no reload. You can only drag and resize cards while edit mode (Customize) is on; the rest of the time the layout is locked.\n\n## How Your Layout and Refresh Work\n\n**Your layout sticks.** Your card arrangement is saved to your account, so it follows you across sessions and devices. It saves automatically whenever you move, resize, add, or remove a card in edit mode. **Reset** (in edit mode) clears your custom layout and rebuilds the standard one. Focus Mode is remembered separately, and you can bookmark or share the page while it's on so it reopens straight into Focus Mode.\n\n**Staying current.** The first time the dashboard opens it shows a brief loading screen. After that it quietly refreshes itself every **5 minutes** in the background — no loading screen, so the page never flickers while you work. This stops when you leave the page. Ambient Mode refreshes on its own faster schedule (see below).\n\n## Auto-Ambient Idle Timeout\n\nThe dashboard can switch to Ambient Mode on its own after you've been idle for a while, and you choose how long that wait is. It's **Off by default** — auto-ambient is something you opt into. The choices are: Off, 1 minute, 5 minutes, 15 minutes, 30 minutes, or 1 hour. The dashboard treats any mouse movement, click, key press, touch, or scroll as activity, so the timer only counts true idle time; with the setting Off it never switches on its own. When the idle time is reached, it switches to Ambient Mode **only if** you're not already in Ambient Mode, not in Focus Mode, and not editing your layout — so it never interrupts what you're doing. Pressing Escape or clicking anywhere leaves Ambient Mode and resets the idle timer. While in Ambient Mode, the display refreshes its numbers every **60 seconds** and updates the clock every second.\n\n## What Action Items Can Flag\n\nThe Action Items card lists follow-ups the system raises for you. Each one has an icon that matches what it's about. The kinds of follow-ups you may see:\n\n- **Quote about to expire**\n- **Stale lead** (no recent contact)\n- **Invoice past due**\n- **Delivery at risk**\n- **Cost overrun**\n- **Certification about to expire**\n- **Maintenance due**\n- **Failed quality check**\n- **Return received**\n- **Sales order confirmed**\n- **Ready to ship**\n- **Materials ready**\n- **Shipment delivered**\n\nFollow-ups are sorted by due date, soonest first (ones with no due date fall to the end), and the card shows up to **8** at once, with a 'more' link when there are additional ones. Each row links to the record it's about, flags an overdue due date, and gives you a checkmark to complete it and an X to dismiss it — both of which clear the row right away. The card lists only open follow-ups and shows a friendly message when there are none.","sections":[]}"""
        });

